Usage Instructions
1. Start the Daemon
Run the daemon in the background (or add it to your Niri startup):

bash
./nsm.py --daemon &
2. Save a Session
To capture the current state:

bash
./nsm.py --save
The state is saved to ~/.cache/niri-session.json.

3. Restore a Session
To restore all windows to their correct workspaces:

bash
./nsm.py --restore
Recommended Niri Keybinds
Add these to your config.kdl to make saving and restoring seamless:

kdl
binds {
    // Save session snapshot
    "Mod+Ctrl+S" { spawn "/home/kenn/Projects/Niri-Session-Manager/nsm.py" "--save"; }
    // Restore session snapshot
    "Mod+Ctrl+R" { spawn "/home/kenn/Projects/Niri-Session-Manager/nsm.py" "--restore"; }
}
Verification Results
 CLI Parsing: Verified via --help.
 Executability: Fixed permissions with chmod +x.
 Architecture: Unified the best parts of all 4 previous scripts.